<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_baræg" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>baræg</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>всадник</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>horseman</q></cit></sense><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_baræg." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>farast baræǵy</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>девять всадников</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>ten horsemen</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>65</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>æz baræg næ dæn</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>я не наездник</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>I am not a horseman</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>14</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>saw bæxyl saw baræg</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>на черном коне черный всадник</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>there is a black horseman on a black horse</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_ОТ"/><biblScope>32</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>farast baræǵy</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>девять всадников</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>ten horsemen</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>65</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>æz baræg næ dæn</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>я не наездник</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>I am not a horseman</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>14</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>saw bæxyl saw baræg</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>на черном коне черный всадник</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>there is a black horseman on a black horse</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_ОТ"/><biblScope>32</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к *%ibāraka%i-, от не сохранившегося самостоятельно глагола %ibār-%i [см. <xr><ref target="#entry_*bar"/></xr>] ‘ездить верхом’ (как <xr><ref target="#entry_maræg"/></xr> ‘убийца’ от %imar%i- [см. <xr/>], <xr><ref target="#entry_daræg"/></xr> ‘кормилец’ от %idar%i- [см. <xr/>], <xr><ref target="#entry_zaræg"/></xr> ‘певец’ от zar- [см. <xr/>]). Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>bar-</w><gloss><q>ездить верхом</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>asa-bāra-</w><gloss><q>всадник</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>asa</w><gloss><q>лошадь</q></gloss></mentioned>). Из многочисленных других иранских соответствий можно отметить: <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/><w>vār-</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="yai"><w>vōra</w><gloss><q>всадник</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<bibl><biblScope>Тр. Тадж. базы АН СССР 1940 IX 103</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*βārāk</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>*βārē(β'r'k, β'ryh)</w><gloss><q>всадник</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>βārākčīk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>*βārēčīk</w><gloss><q>верховая лошадь</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (см.: <bibl><ref target="#ref_Henning._BBB"/><biblScope>54</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>bārgya-</w><gloss><q>всадник</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w>bāraa</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>верховое животное</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w>aśśa-bāraa</w><gloss><q>всадник</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>bārak</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>bāragī</w><gloss><q>лошадь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"><lang/><w>wərok</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="srh"><w>worak</w><gloss><q>лошадь</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/><w>worj</w><gloss><q>лошадь</q></gloss></mentioned>. — К осетинскому примыкает <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/><w>berij</w></mentioned> (← %ibaræg%i), <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>bärij</w><gloss><q>молодец</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w/><gloss><q>удалец</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><w/><gloss><q>джигит</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (как <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>merij</w><gloss><q>убийца</q></gloss></mentioned> из <xr><ref target="#entry_maræg"/></xr>). — Исчезновению глагола <xr><ref target="#entry_*bar"/></xr> в значении ‘ездить верхом’ способствовало, вероятно, то, что в осетинском есть еще два глагола такого же звучания: <xr><ref target="#entry_baryn"/></xr> ‘взвешивать’ и <xr><ref target="#entry_baryn"/></xr> ‘прощать’. Ср. <xr><ref target="#entry_bajrag"/></xr> ‘жеребенок’, а также <xr><ref target="#entry_bal"/></xr> и <xr><ref target="#entry_balc"/></xr>.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 50</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>27</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>57</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to *%ibāraka%i-, from the verb %ibār%i- [see <xr><ref target="#entry_*bar"/></xr>] ‘ride’ which is not in usage anymore (like <xr><ref target="#entry_maræg"/></xr> ‘killer’ from %imar%i- [see <xr><ref target="#entry_maryn"/></xr>], <xr><ref target="#entry_daræg"/></xr> ‘feeder’ from %idar%i- [see <xr><ref target="#entry_daryn"/></xr>], <xr><ref target="#entry_zaræg"/></xr> ‘singer’ from %izar%i- [see <xr><ref target="#entry_zaryn"/></xr>]). Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>bar-</w><gloss><q>ride</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>asa-bāra-</w><gloss><q>horseman</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/><w>asa</w><gloss><q>horse</q></gloss></mentioned>). There should be mentioned the following Iranian correspondences among others: <mentioned xml:lang="yai"><lang/><w>vār-</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="yai"><w>vōra</w><gloss><q>horseman</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (<bibl><biblScope>Trudy Tadžikskoj bazy AN SSSR 1940 IX 103</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>*βārāk</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>*βārē(β'r'k, β'ryh)</w><gloss><q>horseman</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>βārākčīk</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>*βārēčīk</w><gloss><q>riding horse</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (see: <bibl><ref target="#ref_Henning._BBB"/><biblScope>54</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>bārgya-</w><gloss><q>horseman</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w>bāraa</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>riding animal</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><w>aśśa-bāraa</w><gloss><q>horseman</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>bārak</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/><w>bāragī</w><gloss><q>horse</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"><lang/><w>wərok</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="srh"><w>worak</w><gloss><q>horse</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="sgh"><lang/><w>worj</w><gloss><q>horse</q></gloss></mentioned>. — The following words are close to Ossetic: <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/><w>berij</w></mentioned> (← %ibaræg%i), <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>bärij</w><gloss><q>good person</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w/><gloss><q>daredevil</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang=""><w/><gloss><q>jigit</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (like <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/><w>merij</w><gloss><q>killer</q></gloss></mentioned> from <xr><ref target="#entry_maræg"/></xr>). — The loss of the verb <xr><ref target="#entry_*bar"/></xr> in the meaning 'ride' was made real because of two Ossetic verbs of the same pronounciation: <xr><ref target="#entry_baryn"/></xr> ‘weigh’ and <xr><ref target="#entry_baryn"/></xr> ‘forgive’. Cf. <xr><ref target="#entry_bajrag"/></xr> ‘foal’, and also <xr><ref target="#entry_bal"/></xr> and <xr><ref target="#entry_balc"/></xr>.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 50</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>27</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>57</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>